<h2>I. TikTok Advertising Opportunities and Challenges in Global Markets</h2>
<p>TikTok has become one of the world's fastest-growing short video platforms, with over 1.5 billion monthly active users globally across 150+ countries as of 2024. For brands expanding internationally, TikTok ads represent a critical channel to reach Gen Z and Millennial consumers. However, as competition intensifies, advertising costs continue rising—eMarketer data shows TikTok's CPM (Cost Per Mille) increased approximately 35% year-over-year in 2024, demanding more sophisticated advertising strategies.</p>
<p><strong>Article Objective</strong>: Help overseas businesses achieve <strong>150%-300% ROI improvement</strong> through refined operational strategies under limited budgets.</p>
<hr />
<h2>II. Account Setup and Configuration</h2>
<h3>2.1 Account Structure Design Principles</h3>
<p>A well-structured TikTok ad account forms the foundation of successful campaigns. Adopt a <strong>"Campaign-AdSet-Ad" three-tier architecture</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Campaign Level</strong>: Segregate by marketing objectives (brand awareness, app installs, sales conversions)</li>
<li><strong>AdSet Level</strong>: Segment by audience characteristics or creative types</li>
<li><strong>Ad Level</strong>: Deploy 3-5 creatives per AdSet for testing</li>
</ul>
<h3>2.2 Pixel Installation and Event Tracking</h3>
<p>TikTok Pixel is essential for optimization. Key installation points:</p>
<ol>
<li>Deploy base code across all critical website pages</li>
<li>Configure core conversion events (recommended priority: Purchase &gt; AddToCart &gt; ViewContent)</li>
<li>Use TikTok Events Manager to verify event firing accuracy</li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Case Study</strong>: A consumer electronics brand missed installing Pixel on checkout pages, preventing the system from learning high-value user behaviors. Their CPA ran 42% above target. After completing installation, CPA dropped to 85% of target within two weeks.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>2.3 Budget Allocation Strategy</h3>
<p>For new accounts, apply the <strong>"20-20-60 Rule"</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>20% budget</strong>: Testing new audiences and creatives</li>
<li><strong>20% budget</strong>: Scaling verified high-performing combinations</li>
<li><strong>60% budget</strong>: Stable delivery of optimized ad groups</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>III. Audience Targeting: From Broad to Precision</h2>
<h3>3.1 Basic Targeting Parameters</h3>
<p>TikTok's ad platform offers multiple targeting dimensions:</p>
