<h3>5.2 Bidding Strategy Selection</h3>
<p>TikTok ads offer three bidding approaches:</p>
<p><strong>① Lowest Cost</strong>:<br />
- System finds lowest bid automatically<br />
- Ideal for testing phases to quickly gain exposure<br />
- Drawback: Cost volatility</p>
<p><strong>② Target Cost</strong>:<br />
- Set desired cost per action<br />
- System delivers volume while maintaining target cost<br />
- <strong>Recommended for scaling phases</strong></p>
<p><strong>③ Bid Cap</strong>:<br />
- Set maximum bid limit<br />
- Suitable for limited budgets requiring cost control<br />
- Drawback: May not achieve volume targets</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Practical Tip</strong>: Run new ads on Lowest Cost for first 3 days to accumulate data. Switch to Target Cost once <strong>20-30 conversions</strong> are achieved to stabilize CPA.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>5.3 Scheduling and Frequency Control</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ad Scheduling</strong>: Set based on target market peak hours; for European/American markets, recommend <strong>9PM-9AM Beijing time</strong></li>
<li><strong>Frequency Cap</strong>: Limit single user exposure to <strong>max 3 times/day, 7 times/week</strong></li>
<li><strong>Ad Fatigue Management</strong>: Creative lifecycle typically <strong>7-14 days</strong>; continuously refresh creatives</li>
</ul>
